VALUES
(41, 10, 13, 5, 31, 12, 13, 'children', 'Children and Learning', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of children in learning and receiving blessings. Mark 10:13 shows children being brought to Jesus for his touch, while Deuteronomy 31:12-13 calls for children to gather and learn about the Lord.', 'theme', 0.293, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 13, 29, 2, 16, 16, NULL, 'Children in Community Context', 'Both passages emphasize the inclusion of children in communal gatherings. Mark highlights the importance of bringing children to Jesus, while Joel calls for the gathering of children as part of a larger assembly.', 'theme', 0.286, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 13, 41, 9, 38, 38, 'rebuked those that brought them', 'Rebuking and Exclusion Themes', 'This connection highlights the theme of rebuking those who seek to approach Jesus. In both passages, the disciples exhibit a tendency to exclude others, whether children or those casting out demons, based on their perceived in-group status.', 'theme', 0.286, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 13, 41, 10, 48, 48, NULL, 'Children and Crying Out', 'This connection highlights the theme of individuals seeking Jesus'' attention. In both passages, there is a contrast between those who attempt to silence others and the persistent cries for Jesus'' mercy.', 'theme', 0.286, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 14, 40, 18, 4, 4, 'little children', 'Children and Humility in the Kingdom', 'This connection highlights the significance of children in relation to the kingdom of God. Both passages emphasize the value of humility, as seen in the phrase ''little children'' and the call to ''humble himself as this little child.''', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 14, 40, 19, 14, 14, NULL, 'Children and the Kingdom Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of allowing children to come to Jesus, highlighting their significance in relation to the kingdom of God/heaven. The phrases used in both verses are nearly identical, reinforcing this shared theme.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 14, 19, 131, 1, 2, NULL, 'Childlike Humility and Acceptance', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of humility and childlike qualities. Mark 10:14 highlights the value of children in the kingdom of God, while Psalms 131:1-2 reflects a child''s quietness and dependence. This connection highlights the theme of approaching God with a humble heart.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 14, 42, 18, 15, 16, NULL, 'Children and the Kingdom of God', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' call for children to come to him, highlighting their significance in the kingdom of God. The repetition of the phrase ''Suffer little children to come unto me'' reinforces this theme.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 14, 60, 2, 2, 2, 'little children', 'Children and Spiritual Growth', 'This connection highlights the theme of spiritual growth through innocence and dependence. Both passages emphasize the importance of approaching faith with a childlike attitude, as seen in ''little children'' and ''newborn babes.''', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 14, 46, 14, 20, 20, 'children', 'Understanding and Childlike Faith', 'This connection highlights the contrast between childlike faith and mature understanding. Both passages emphasize the importance of being childlike in certain aspects, while also urging maturity in understanding.', 'theme', 0.356, 'medium', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 14, 55, 3, 15, 15, 'little children to come unto me', 'Children and Scripture Connection', 'This connection highlights the importance of children in both passages. Mark emphasizes allowing children to come to Jesus, while 2 Timothy notes that knowing the scriptures from a young age leads to wisdom and salvation.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 15, 40, 18, 3, 3, NULL, 'Childlike Faith in the Kingdom', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of becoming ''as little children'' to enter the kingdom of God. This connection highlights the theme of humility and innocence required for acceptance into the divine realm.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 15, 42, 18, 17, 17, 'as a little child', 'Childlike Reception of the Kingdom', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of receiving the kingdom of God ''as a little child.'' This connection highlights the consistent teaching across the Gospels regarding the attitude required for entering the kingdom.', 'parallel', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 15, 43, 3, 3, 6, 'receive the kingdom of God as a little child', 'Childlike Reception of the Kingdom', 'Both passages emphasize the necessity of a transformative experience to enter the kingdom of God. Mark highlights receiving the kingdom as a little child, while John speaks of being born again, suggesting a similar theme of humility and newness.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 16, 23, 40, 11, 11, 'blessed them', 'Shepherding and Blessing Imagery', 'Both passages emphasize the nurturing aspect of care, with Jesus blessing the children and the shepherd gathering lambs. The imagery of carrying and blessing reflects a deep compassion and guidance for the vulnerable.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 16, 41, 9, 36, 36, 'took them up in his arms', 'Connection of Jesus and Children', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' actions with children, highlighting his care and blessing. In each instance, he takes a child into his arms, demonstrating his affection and importance of children in his ministry.', 'theme', 0.321, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 16, 1, 48, 14, 16, 'blessed them', 'Blessing and Laying on Hands', 'Both passages emphasize the act of blessing through the laying on of hands. In Mark, Jesus blesses the children, while in Genesis, Israel blesses Ephraim and Manasseh with a deliberate hand placement.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 16, 5, 28, 3, 3, 'blessed them', 'Blessing in Both Passages', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of blessing, with Mark 10:16 depicting Jesus blessing children and Deuteronomy 28:3 outlining blessings in various aspects of life. This connection highlights the significance of divine favor and care.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 16, 42, 2, 28, 34, 'blessed them', 'Blessing and Embrace of Children', 'Both passages emphasize the act of taking someone in arms and blessing them. In Mark, Jesus blesses children, while in Luke, Simeon takes Jesus in his arms and blesses God, highlighting the significance of blessing in both contexts.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 16, 42, 24, 50, 51, 'blessed them', 'Blessing and Ascension Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the act of blessing, with Jesus lifting his hands to bless those around him. This connection highlights the continuity of Jesus'' ministry from childhood to his ascension.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 16, 43, 21, 15, 17, 'blessed them', 'Connection of Care and Nurturing', 'Both passages emphasize the care for the vulnerable, with Jesus blessing children in Mark and instructing Peter to ''Feed my lambs'' in John. This connection highlights the importance of nurturing and guiding those who are spiritually young or in need.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 17, 40, 19, 16, 30, 'what shall I do that I may inherit eternal life?', 'Eternal Life Inquiry Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the question of how to inherit eternal life. The young man''s inquiry in both texts leads to a discussion on the requirements for salvation and the challenges faced by the wealthy.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 17, 42, 18, 18, 30, 'what shall I do that I may inherit eternal life?', 'Inquiry about Eternal Life', 'Both passages emphasize a man''s inquiry about inheriting eternal life. The question posed in Mark 10:17 is mirrored in Luke 18:18, establishing a direct thematic connection between the two accounts.', 'theme', 0.44699999999999995, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 17, 45, 2, 7, 7, 'that I may inherit eternal life', 'Eternal Life Pursuit', 'Both passages emphasize the quest for eternal life. The inquiry in Mark 10:17 about inheriting eternal life parallels the pursuit of eternal life through well-doing in Romans 2:7.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 17, 43, 6, 27, 28, 'what shall I do that I may inherit eternal life?', 'Seeking Eternal Life', 'Both passages emphasize the pursuit of eternal life. In Mark, the question is about inheriting eternal life, while in John, the focus is on working for food that endures unto everlasting life.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 17, 42, 10, 25, 25, NULL, 'Inquiry about Eternal Life', 'Both passages emphasize a question about inheriting eternal life. The phrase ''what shall I do to inherit eternal life'' appears in both, highlighting a common theme of seeking guidance on salvation.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 17, 45, 10, 2, 4, 'what shall I do that I may inherit eternal life?', 'Seeking Eternal Life and Righteousness', 'This connection highlights the pursuit of eternal life in Mark 10:17 and the quest for righteousness in Romans 10:2-4. Both passages emphasize the need for divine righteousness rather than self-established means to achieve salvation.', 'theme', 0.34199999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 17, 44, 2, 37, 37, 'what shall I do', 'Inquiry About Eternal Life', 'Both passages emphasize a question about what actions are necessary for salvation. The rich young ruler asks, ''what shall I do that I may inherit eternal life?'' while the people in Acts inquire, ''what shall we do?''', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 18, 42, 18, 19, 19, 'Why callest thou me good?', 'Connection of Goodness in Jesus'' Teachings', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of goodness, stating that only God is truly good. The phrasing in both verses is nearly identical, reinforcing the idea that Jesus redirects the notion of goodness to God alone.', 'parallel', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(41, 10, 18, 40, 19, 17, 17, 'there is none good but one, that is, God', 'Connection of Goodness and Commandments', 'Both passages emphasize the concept of goodness, stating that only God is truly good. They also connect this idea to the importance of keeping the commandments for eternal life.', 'theme', 0.40499999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
